<br>=0D<br>Authorities in Ibanda district [Western Region] have enforced a<=
br>quarantine on the movement of cattle and the sale of animal products<br>=
following an outbreak of anthrax.=0D<br>=0D<br>According to the Ibanda Dist=
rict Chief Administrative Officer Ruhemba<br>Kweronda, the district has reg=
istered sporadic cases of anthrax<br>disease in humans who are suspected to=
 have handled meat from infected<br>dead animals.=0D<br>=0D<br>Kweronda say=
s the disease that was first noticed in November last year<br>[2023] was re=
ported in Rugaaga 1 and IV villages of Keihangara Sub<br>County, where 9 pe=
ople who confessed to having slaughtered a dead<br>animal tested positive f=
or anthrax.=0D<br>=0D<br>He adds that early this month [January 2024] one p=
erson from Mbonwa<br>Parish Rukiri Sub County tested positive and currently=
 12 people from<br>Kakoma are showing signs. He also said that 2 animals di=
ed abruptly in<br>Kigarama ward Ibanda Municipality and samples have been c=
ollected and<br>taken to the laboratory.=0D<br>=0D<br>According to Kweronda=
, all slaughter activities and movement of<br>livestock will be temporarily=
 enforced for one month in Ibanda<br>Municipality and Ibanda South Constitu=
ency.=0D<br>=0D<br>He says other measures put in place to curb the spread o=
f the disease<br>include registering all meat handlers in the district, enf=
orcing the<br>requirement by all cattle traders to have cattle trading lice=
nses<br>issued by the Ministry of Animal Husbandry, carrying out ring<br>va=
ccination of all suspected animal species in areas of Keihangara sub<br>cou=
nty Bisheshe Division, Rukiri Sub County and Kagongo division, but<br>also =
continued sensitization and surveillance activities.=0D<br>=0D<br>Dr Hillar=
y Arinaitwe, the District Veterinary Officer says that they<br>have written=
 to the Ministry of Agriculture demanding vaccines.=0D<br>=0D<br>In Decembe=
r [2023], authorities in Kyotera district enforced a<br>complete ban on the=
 movement of livestock and its products to halt the<br>spread of anthrax.=0D=
<br>=0D<br>For nearly a month, the district has grappled with a rare outbre=
ak of<br>anthrax. This outbreak has claimed at least 6 lives and led to sev=
eral<br>hospitalizations.=0D<br>=0D<br>Anthrax is a zoonotic caused by _Bac=
illus anthracis_, a spore-like<br>bacteria that produces strong toxins that=
 are dangerous to animals and<br>humans. Ruminants such as cows, goats, and=
 sheep can quickly die with<br>their carcasses showing little signs of infe=
ction but in human beings,<br>symptoms begin with a flu-like illness, raise=
d boil-like lesions on<br>the skin.=0D<br>=0D<br>Meanwhile, officials in Ki=
ruhura District have extended the closure of<br>4 animal markets to control=
 the spread of foot and mouth disease in<br>the district.=0D<br>=0D<br>The =
4 markets are Nyakasahara, Kyiebuza, Kyeshama livestock markets,<br>and Kit=
ura goat Market.=0D<br>=0D<br>In the Circular from the Kiruhura District Ch=
ief Administrative<br>Officer Charles Kiberu Nsubuga, to all lower local co=
uncil<br>chairpersons dated 12 Jan 2024, they should ensure continued<br>en=
forcement of the directive.=0D<br>=0D<br>--=0D<br>Communicated by:=0D<br>Pr=
